{{about||the razor equipment|Razor strop|other uses|Strap (disambiguation)}} A '''strap''', sometimes also called '''strop''', is an elongated [[wikt:flap|flap]] or [[ribbon]], usually of [[Cloth|fabric]] or [[leather]].
Thin straps are used as part of [[clothing]] or [[baggage]], or bedding such as a [[sleeping bag]]. See for example [[spaghetti strap]], [[shoulder strap]]. A strap differs from a [[belt (clothing)|belt]] mainly in that a strap is usually integral to the item of clothing; either can be used in combination with [[buckle]]s.
Straps are also used as [[fastener]]s to attach and bind items, to objects, animals (for example a [[saddle]] on a horse) and people (for example a [[watch]] on a [[wrist]]), or even to tie down people and animals, as on an apparatus for [[corporal punishment]]. Occasionally a strap is specified after what it binds or holds, e.g. chin strap.
Mere two-inch-wide nylon vehicle tow/recovery straps are commonly rated at 20,000 lbs. break strength.<ref>{{cite web |title=2 inch nylon strap: Tow Capacity: 10,000 lbs, Break Strength: 20,000 lbs; larger sizes |url=http://www.uscargocontrol.com/Towing-Auto-Hauling/Recovery-Straps-Tow-Straps |publisher=uscargocontrol.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Various tow straps, ropes, etc, with specifications |url=http://www2.northerntool.com/towing/tow-chains-ropes-straps-2.htm |publisher=northerntool.com}}</ref> [[Webbing]] is a particular type of strap that is a strong fabric woven as a flat strip or tube that is also often used in place of [[rope]]. Modern webbing is typically made from exceptionally high-strength material, and is used in automobile [[seat belts]], furniture manufacturing, transportation, towing, military apparel, cargo fasteners, and many other fields.
==Packaging== {{Main|Strapping}}
Strap is commonly used in the [[packaging]] industry to secure or fasten items. It may be made from a wide range of materials, such as [[plastic]], [[steel]], [[paper]], or [[fabric]]. Usually the strap is secured to itself through various means, but it may also be secured to other items, such as [[pallet]]s.
