Attenders wear evening attire, which is specified on the invitation as ''[[black tie]]'' or ''[[white tie]]'' (the most formal){{Citation needed|date=November 2010}}. [[Social dance]] forms a large part of the evening; actual [[ballroom dancing]] may or may not occur.
==Etymology== The word "ball" derives from the Latin word ''ballare'', meaning "to dance"; the Latin word also developed into [[French language|French]] ''baller''—from where it swapped into languages like English or German—, and ''bailar'', the [[Spanish language|Spanish]] and [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] verbs for "to dance" (although all three Romance languages also know ''danser'', ''danzar'' and ''dançar'' respectively). [[Catalan language|Catalan]] uses the same word, ''ball'', for the dance event.
