{{Redirect|High school reunion|other uses|High School Reunion (disambiguation){{!}}High School Reunion}} {{redirect|School reunion|the Doctor Who episode|School Reunion (Doctor Who)}} {{other uses|Class Reunion (disambiguation)}} {{Unreferenced|date=September 2008}} [[Image:YaleClassOf1835ClassReunionNotice1850.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Class reunion invitation, Yale College, 1850]] A '''class reunion''' is a meeting of former classmates, typically organized at or near their former [[school]] by one or a group of the class members on or around an anniversary of their graduation, e.g. 5 years later. Former teachers may be invited as well. They reminisce about their school days and bring each other up to date on what has happened since they went their separate ways.
Some class reunions also include a reunion class gift to the institution. [[File:CALUMET HS CLASS OF 67 DSC01900.JPG|thumb|right|people in class reunion of [[Calumet High School (Calumet, Michigan)|Calumet High School]], Michigan]] [[File:Maturatreffen1975c.jpg|thumb|right|class reunion in Vienna with the participation of former teachers]] ==Class reunions in film and literature== In [[film]] and [[literature]], especially [[comedy]], [[crime fiction|crime novels]], [[Thriller (genre)|thriller]]s, and psychological suspense novels, class reunions have been a frequent device used to show the eruption of [[emotion]]s such as [[shame]], [[hatred]], and [[guilt (emotion)|guilt]] within individual characters who, suddenly faced again with their own youth, become aware that they have been unable to cope with their past. In many cases, those who used to be [[bullying|bullied]], humiliated, or in some other way mistreated by their teachers or classmates believe that now their chance has come to take [[revenge]] on their former torturers. Participants often nostalgically reminisce about their old school days or fondly remember their school [[prank]]s. Alumni are quite often concerned about how their lives have turned out when compared with the lives of their former classmates, and will sometimes feel pressured enough to go to great lengths to concoct stories about their fruitful careers, personal accomplishments, and relationships with others.
Another staple of this kind of fiction is former classmates taking up with their old flames again, either because they have changed to their advantage and developed into an admirable adult or precisely for the opposite reason&mdash;because they have not changed at all in a fleeting world.
Examples of films revolving around class reunions include: {{multicol}} * ''[[Falling in Love Again (1980 film)|Falling in Love Again]]'' ([[1980 in film|1980]]) * ''[[National Lampoon's Class Reunion]]'' ([[1982 in film|1982]]) * ''[[The Big Chill (film)|The Big Chill]]'' ([[1983 in film|1983]]) * ''[[Peggy Sue Got Married]]'' ([[1986 in film|1986]]) * [[Kenneth Branagh]]'s ''[[Peter's Friends]]'' ([[1992 in film|1992]]) * ''[[Beautiful Girls (film)|Beautiful Girls]]'' ([[1996 in film|1996]]) {{multicol-break}} * [[George Armitage]]'s ''[[Grosse Pointe Blank]]'' ([[1997 in film|1997]]) * [[Romy and Michele's High School Reunion]] ([[1997 in film|1997]]) * ''[[Since You've Been Gone (film)|Since You've Been Gone]]'' ([[1998 in film|1998]]) * ''[[10 Years (film)|10 years]] ([[2011 in film|2011]]) * ''[[American Reunion]]'' ([[2012 in film|2012]]) * ''[[Back in the Day (2014 film)|Back in the Day]]'' ([[2014 in film|2014]]) {{multicol-end}}
Examples of fiction, revolving around class reunions, include: {{multicol}} *[[Tim O'Brien (author)|Tim O'Brien]]'s ''[[July, July]]'' ([[2002 in literature|2002]]) {{multicol-break}} *[[Ben Elton]]'s ''[[Past Mortem]]'' ([[2004 in literature|2004]]) *Paul Reizin's ''Fiends Reunited'' ([[2004 in literature|2004]]) *[[Simone van der Vlugt]]'s ''De reünie'' ([[2004 in literature|2004]]) {{multicol-end}}
Examples of TV shows loosely based on class reunions, include: {{multicol}} *[[The Class of '62]]-episode of the Sitcom [[Only Fools and Horses]] (1991) *[[Mother and Child Reunion (Degrassi: The Next Generation)|Mother and Child Reunion]]-episode of the teen drama [[ Degrassi: The Next Generation]] (2001) *[[GCB (TV series)|GCB]] (2012) {{multicol-end}}
