'''Hammer pants''', a loose fitting [[trousers|trouser]] inspired by [[harem pants]] which originated in the [[Arabian Peninsula]] and are often mistakenly called "[[parachute pants]]", are customized/modified [[Wide leg jeans#History|baggy pants]] tapered at the ankle with a [[Sagging (fashion)#Origin|sagging]] rise made suitable for [[Hip-hop dance|hip-hop dancing]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Sagging Crotches: MC Hammer / Harem Pants|url=http://www.theurbangent.com/2009/01/sagging-crotches-mc-hammer-harem-pants.html|work=The Urban Gentleman}}</ref>
Hammer pants were [[Hip hop fashion#Late 1980s to early 1990s fashion|popularized in the 1980s and 1990s]] by rapper [[Stanley Burrell]] who would [[Entertainer#Dance|entertain/dance]] in them during live [[concert]]s and [[music video]]s, hence his [[stage name]], [[MC Hammer|(M.C.) Hammer]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Chance|first=Molly|title=American Music Awards 2012 fashion: Justin Bieber, Chris Brown and M.C. Hammer's saggy drawers|url=http://blog.zap2it.com/pop2it/2012/11/american-music-awards-2012-fashion-justin-bieber-chris-brown-and-mc-hammers-saggy-drawers.html|work=Zap2it|publisher=Tribune Media Services, Inc.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Oldenburg|first=Ann|title=Justin Bieber switches from saggy to skinny|url=http://www.usatoday.com/story/life/people/2013/01/14/justin-bieber-answers-saggy-pants-criticism/1833731/|work=USA Today|publisher=USA Today}}</ref>
[[MC_Hammer#Legacy and pop culture fame|Hammer's specialized clothing line]] would come in a variety of colors and were usually [[1990s in fashion#Hip-hop 2|shiny and flashy]]-styled, as seen throughout his hip-hop career during [[talk show]] appearances, concerts, music videos and again on his own [[Reality television#Documentary-style|TV reality show]] in 2009 called ''[[Hammertime]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Leo|first=Alex|title=MC Hammer Flash Mob: Parachute-Pant-Wearing Dancers Take Over Store On Sunset (VIDEO)|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2009/06/07/mc-hammer-flash-mob-parac_n_212268.html|work=Huffington Post|publisher=The Huffington Post}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nypost.com/p/blogs/item_jtDJBpaGfHUGtsVdRXa85L | archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20111129112126/http://www.nypost.com/p/blogs/item_jtDJBpaGfHUGtsVdRXa85L | archivedate=2011-11-29 | title =MC Hammer: 'Get Ready For a Big Reunion With Me and Vanilla Ice' | work = [[New York Post]] |first=Ryan |last=Brockington |date=2009-08-06 }}</ref>
